#
# Diagnostic and test script for the org.freedesktop.secrets Secret Service
# protocol.  Works with any compliant implementation: KeePassXC, GNOME
# Keyring, KWallet Secret Service bridge, etc.
#
# Uses Gio.DBusProxy throughout for correct interface negotiation.
#
# COMMANDS
# --------
#   introspect
#       Print the raw D-Bus introspection XML for /org/freedesktop/secrets.
#       Useful for confirming which interfaces and methods are actually exposed
#       by the running Secret Service implementation.
#
#   list [--verbose]
#       List all items in the default collection.  Prints label and UserName
#       attribute for each entry, sorted by label.  With --verbose, prints all
#       attributes for each item.  No secrets are fetched.
#
#   lookup <key>
#       Look up the item whose label exactly matches <key> and print its
#       secret to stdout.  <key> is the entry title as shown in KeePassXC.
#
# USAGE
# -----
#   python3 docs/dev/kwin_secret_service.py introspect
#   python3 docs/dev/kwin_secret_service.py list
#   python3 docs/dev/kwin_secret_service.py list --verbose
#   python3 docs/dev/kwin_secret_service.py lookup "root@m68"
#
# OPTIONS
#   --collection PATH   Override the collection D-Bus path.
#                       Default: /org/freedesktop/secrets/aliases/default
